Julia Veenstra has created an absolute statement piece with "Survival" once again!

This massive 40x72 painting captures Julia's wide brushstrokes perfectly. The detail that's packed into this painting is breathtaking, and the longer you gaze at it, the more you discover!

"Survival" features a dense shoreline forest full of rich colours and an adventurous branching-out tree growing outwards over the lake! The lush green plant life, combined with Julia's beautiful blue sky, pair together wonderfully, creating her unmistakable artistic style, which she is famous for!

“Kenisis Adventure” is a perfect display of Julia Veenstra’s vibrant colour and bold brush strokes on such a large canvas!

Hello! I have a few new followers so I thought I would tell you a little more about myself!
My name is Julia Veenstra and I live and work in Hamilton, Ontario!  #Hamilton has been very, very kind to me! 

I am an artist, wife and mother to 5.(10 now with spouses) and 8 grandchildren!

I attended Sheridan college many years ago and worked briefly at a publishing house before starting at home with my children.  I painted when I had commissions as who has time with 5 kids to just play!?

We lived in the States for a while and spent 5 years in East Africa, Tanzania and Kenya to be exact. I taught art at an international school in Kenya. I can speak some Swahili! Habari Yako!?

Upon returning to Canada I took a gallery space and began my art career!
Social media has also been kind!

I am currently opening a new gallery and cafe! @crownandpressgallery  Follow along if you will!

I have learned so much in the last 20 years. I have a course to teach it and with the course I have a mentoring group! Link in bio! Join me! 

I have also learned a lot about opening a gallery and cafe. I can help you with yours if you want! Lol. 

So my question is this… Who are you and what have you learned from your journey?

Something I learned about myself is that I am a terrible employee.  After my stint in college I had a job at a book publishing firm and hated it! I did not like the 9-5. I am realizing it now that for ten years I also had “Available by Appointment or Chance” on my door to my old studio on James Street in Hamilton. I did not like set hours to be the boss of me! 

I think my self realization and acknowledgment of being a bad employee left room for me to be a good entrepreneur.  Not limited to set hours I find inspiration and opportunity at any moment. 

Don’t let anything define you. You do you!

My next @squarefootshow will be just that. A curated collection of artists doing what they do best! That show is coming up end of November. 

This piece is in progress and will be done when I feel like it! Lol!
